`Iterator::map` transforms each item from an iterator with a closure.

```rust
fn main() {
    let nums = vec![1, 2, 3];
    let doubled: Vec<i32> = nums.iter().map(|n| n * 2).collect();
    println!("{:?}", doubled);
}
```

This prints `[2, 4, 6]`.

Use `Option::unwrap_or` when you want a default value if an `Option` is `None`.

```rust
fn main() {
    let port: Option<u16> = None;
    let port = port.unwrap_or(8080);
    println!("{port}");
}
```

If the option is `Some(value)`, that value is returned instead.
